<p>A friend emailed with subject line &ldquo;what are you
doing?&rdquo;&mdash;no body. Obviously there&rsquo;s a ton of ways to answer
that. I decided to take it as an opportunity to provide a report on how
I&rsquo;ve actually spent my time since <a
    href="http://blog.gittip.com/post/27072581481/i-believe-in-gittip">leaving
    YouGov</a>. I keep pretty good track of my time (&ldquo;<a
    href="http://www.paulgraham.com/13sentences.html">you make what you
    measure</a>&rdquo;), and since others may also have the same
question&mdash;especially my patrons on Gittip&mdash;I&rsquo;m posting it here
on my blog.</p>

<p>I&rsquo;ve spent 700 hours on the clock since August 1. I took a week of
vacation in early August, so call it 12 weeks. That&rsquo;s 58 hours per week,
on average. I&rsquo;ve got a wife and four kids and friends and I go to church
most Sundays and sometimes play sax in the evenings&mdash;none of that is in
view here. This is just time on the clock.</p>

